Subject: [PATCH] Add ZDR filter icon and provider exclusions

This patch adds a shield icon to the ZDR filter toggle UI and introduces a
valve to exclude specific providers from ZDR routing/matching.

Highlights:
- Adds a shield icon (data URI) to the ZDR filter toggle in Open WebUI.
- Adds ZDR_EXCLUDED_PROVIDERS valve (comma-separated provider slugs).
- Excludes listed providers from ZDR model matching and auto-attach.
- Applies provider.ignore when ZDR is active to skip excluded providers.

To apply: git apply patches/0007-add-zdr-filter-icon-and-provider-exclusions.patch
To revert: git apply -R patches/0007-add-zdr-filter-icon-and-provider-exclusions.patch

Note: This patch modifies existing upstream files. When upstream updates these
files, you may need to resolve merge conflicts.
